Three
people were killed in a horror crash on the M7 underneath the N2 Bridge in
Durban. Rescue Care
Paramedics found the Corsa Utility bakkie T Boned by a Truck at the intersection. The Bakkie
had five occupants with some seated on the rear of the vehicle. Rescue care
spokesman Garrith Jamieson said the patients were ejected and had sustained
multiple injuries. “One
critically injured passenger was found approximately 40 metres from the point
of impact. advanced life support paramedics worked on the man and placed him on
a ventilator before rushing him to a nearby hospital, where he passed away a
short while later,” Jamieson said. Jamieson
said two occupants were declared dead on the scene and the two others had
sustained serious injuries and were also transported to hospital. “The truck
driver was uninjured,” Jamieson added. At this
stage the events leading up to the collision are unknown.